title: Taylor Swift 'walks off' Tonight Show after forgetting Shake It Off
text:
Taylor Swift could not remember the opening chords of her biggest hit song, Shake It Off, while playing Name that Song on Thursday's The Tonight Show.

After The Roots played the first few bars, host Jimmy Fallon correctly guessed the 29-year-old pop diva's 2014 chart-topping track leaving her stunned in silence.

As the audience roared with laughter, the 10-time Grammy winner hilariously hung her head in shame over not recognizing her own music.

Blanked: Taylor Swift could not remember the opening chords of her biggest hit song, Shake It Off, while playing Name that Song on Thursday's The Tonight Show

The 45-year-old funnyman went from jumping for joy to chasing after Taylor as she pretended to walk off the set.

Swift fared far better when identifying Britney Spears' Baby One More Time, TLC's No Scrubs, and Nelly's Hot in Herre.

'It's Nelly, it's Nelly, it's Nelly's Hot in Herre!' the preppy Pennsylvania-born belter gushed.

'This is my favorite song. Oh yeah, just like, middle school imprints on you.'

The Lover hitmaker also ID-ed Sixpence None The Richer's 1997 song Kiss Me, which she said was 'the first song I learned to play on guitar.'

Taylor was on The Tonight Show promoting her fifth time performing Saturday Night Live this week alongside first-time host, Fleabag star Phoebe Waller-Bridge.

'Ever since I saw Fleabag, I've been all "I can't wait to see this woman host @nbcsnl,"' Swift tweeted on August 26.

'And it's happening now + I get to be there too = I am in shambles.'

Other hosts/musical guests for season 45 include David Harbour and Camila Cabello (October 12); as well as Kristen Stewart (November 2) and Eddie Murphy (December 21).

The Me! singer will then co-headline 97.1 AMP Radio's sold-out seventh annual We Can Survive music festival taking place at the Hollywood Bowl on October 19.

Last year, the 5ft10in blonde signed with Universal Music Group and she plans on releasing her next album in August.
